firmation as to whether the account remains with Prodigy Finance or has been assigned or transferred to any third party. If transferred, please provide the details. \\n\\n\\n\\nHoping to hear from you soon.\\nThank you for your understanding.\\n\\nRegards,\\nTolulope O. Omotayo", "date_and_timestamp": "4/5/2026 18:07", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_2"}, {"message_content": "Good afternoon Andisiwe.\\nI sent an email to Prodigy last Monday and i'm yet to receive a response.\\nMy request is for a payoff statement with some details requested. I am not asking for a settlement offer at this moment as responded to by your AI agent.\\nKindly have a look into the email and let me have the requested information as detailed in my email - Subject: Loan ID PDGUS271931 – Request for Payoff Statement.\\nHoping to hear from you soon.\\nHave a blessed day.\\n\\n\\nRegards,\\nTolulope O. Omotayo", "date_and_timestamp": "4/4/2026 10:09", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_2"}, {"message_content": "Hi Tolulope,\\n \\nFrom point 1-4, I provided a full transactional statement to confirm the relevant information.\\n \\n5. A settlement offer was provided to confirm the settlement amount which is valid till 30 March 2026.\\n \\n6. The current status is delinquent.\\n \\n7. The account is still maintained by Prodigy Finance.\\n \\nWe hope this gives you the clarity you need.\\n \\nIf you need further assistance, please let us know and we’ll be happy to help!\\n \\nKind regards,\\nThaakirah", "date_and_timestamp": "3/5/2026 17:28", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_2"}, {"message_content": "However, my requests are detailed in the letter sent to you.\\nThey are here listed below. The letter is also attached again.\\n \\n\\n1. The original principal amount disbursed to Boston University in December 2021. \\n\\n2. A detailed breakdown of all interest accrued to date, including any capitalized interest. \\n\\n3. A breakdown of any late fees, penalties, or additional charges applied to the account. \\n\\n4. A transaction history showing how my $6,000 payment made in December 2023 was applied (whether to principal, interest, or fees). \\n\\n5. The current total payoff amount as of the date of your response. \\n\\n6. Confirmation of the present status of the account. In that regard, I would like to know the status is current, delinquent, defaulted, charged off, or otherwise. \\n\\n7. Confirmation as to whether the account remains with Prodigy Finance or has been assigned or transferred to any third party. If transferred, please provide the details. \\n\\n\\n\\nHoping to hear from you soon.\\nThank you for your understanding.\\n\\nRegards,\\nTolulope O. Omotayo", "date_and_timestamp": "3/5/2026 15:24", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_2"}, {"message_content": "Good afternoon Andisiwe.\\nI sent an email to Prodigy last Monday and i'm yet to receive a response.\\nMy request is for a payoff statement with some details requested. I am not asking for a settlement offer at this moment as responded to by your AI agent.\\nKindly have a look into the email and let me have the requested information as detailed in my email - Subject: Loan ID PDGUS271931 – Request for Payoff Statement.\\nHoping to hear from you soon.\\nHave a blessed day.\\n\\n\\nRegards,\\nTolulope O. Omotayo", "date_and_timestamp": "3/4/2026 13:21", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_2"}], "_payment_count": 1, "_conversation_count": 7, "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_2"}	\N		9	Customer emails from 4/5/2026 and 3/5/2026 explicitly list 7 points of information required, including transaction history and payoff amount, while rejecting a settlement offer.	Escalate for Agent Review. An agent must manually compile and send the detailed 7-point breakdown requested by the customer to resolve the dispute and unblock payment.	10	The ESCALATION RULES mandate routing to a human when a 'Customer disputes the debt'. The customer's detailed request for information validation qualifies as a dispute that an automated system cannot resolve.		0	The formal calculation based on the last 3 months of payment history is $0, as no payments were received in this period. This may not reflect true capacity, as the customer's request for a payoff statement suggests intent to pay.	0	NO_ACTION	{"willingness": "VERY LOW", "combined_cmd": null, "conversation": "In March and April 2026, the customer has proactively and repeatedly emailed requesting a detailed 7-point breakdown of their account, including a payoff statement and history of a prior payment. They are correcting automated responses and clarifying their need for information, not a settlement offer.", "affordability": "VERY LOW", "customer_guid": "customer_id_2", "vulnerability": false, "ability_to_pay": 0, "internal_action": "", "payment_history": "No payments have been received in the last 3 months. A single payment of $6000 was received on 2023-12-08, which is outside the 3-month analysis window.", "problem_evidence": "Customer emails from 4/5/2026 and 3/5/2026 explicitly list 7 points of information required, including transaction history and payoff amount, while rejecting a settlement offer.", "proposed_solution": "Escalate for Agent Review. An agent must manually compile and send the detailed 7-point breakdown requested by the customer to resolve the dispute and unblock payment.", "solution_evidence": "The ESCALATION RULES mandate routing to a human when a 'Customer disputes the debt'. The customer's detailed request for information validation qualifies as a dispute that an automated system cannot resolve.", "problem_description": "", "arrears_clearance_plan": null, "reason_for_willingness": "Insufficient engagement signals to determine willingness. Defaults to VERY LOW per business rules.", "problem_confidence_score": 9, "reason_for_affordability": "No payments have been received in the last 3 months. As per policy, the estimated monthly payment capacity is $0. With a minimum due of $341, the capacity is 0%, which falls into the VERY LOW category.", "reason_for_vulnerability": "", "reason_for_ability_to_pay": "The formal calculation based on the last 3 months of payment history is $0, as no payments were received in this period. This may not reflect true capacity, as the customer's request for a payoff statement suggests intent to pay.", "solution_confidence_score": 10, "proposed_email_to_customer": "NO_ACTION", "no_of_latest_payments_failed": 0}	pending	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	2026-04-07 09:37:35.378474	88bb298f-0fd9-407b-ad75-1ed7ae2ac794
85	1	1	ed2fbfa1-28fd-4e0f-8e5a-25240eaec5d1	customer_id_3	{"due_date": "2026-04-28", "_payments": [{"amount_paid": "1,211.63", "payment_status": "Cancelled", "date_of_payment": "2026-01-26", "payment_reference": "PAY008", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_3"}, {"amount_paid": "1,211.63", "payment_status": "Cancelled", "date_of_payment": "2026-01-26", "payment_reference": "PAY009", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_3"}], "amount_due": "1920", "dpd_bucket": "60", "minimum_due": "847", "_conversations": [{"message_content": "Hi Darshitaben,\\n \\nThank you for completing the assessment.\\n \\nOur specialist team has kindly requested the most recent three months bank statements.\\n \\nKindly ensure that the requested information is submitted to us before 28 February 2026. You may reply directly to this email.\\n \\nTake care,\\nMpho", "date_and_timestamp": "3/26/2026 13:49", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_3"}, {"message_content": "Hi Darshitaben,\\n \\nThank you for completing the assessment.\\n \\nOur specialist team has kindly requested the most recent three months bank statements.\\n \\nKindly ensure that the requested information is submitted to us before 28 February 2026. You may reply directly to this email.\\n \\nTake care,\\nMpho", "date_and_timestamp": "2/26/2026 13:49", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_3"}, {"message_content": "Dear Prodigy Finance Collections/Payments Team,\\n\\nI am writing to formally address the overdue status of my account (Loan ID: PDGUS493193 & PDGUS551765). I am currently 90 days past due on my installments, and I am reaching out to resolve this situation before the account moves toward default proactively.\\n\\nI am currently experiencing severe financial hardship due to involuntary unemployment following the completion of my studies. Despite an intensive job search, I have not yet secured a stable income. As an international graduate, I am committed to fulfilling my debt obligations, but my current lack of liquidity makes it impossible to meet the standard monthly installments at this moment.\\n\\nI value my relationship with Prodigy Finance and wish to keep my account in good standing. I would like to request the following formally:\\n\\n1.\\nA temporary suspension of payments for the next few months to allow me to finalize my employment search.\\n2.\\nI request a restructuring of my loan terms. This could include extending the total loan tenure to reduce monthly installments or moving to \\"interest-only\\" payments for a set period.\\n\\nI am eager to cooperate with your team. I can provide documentation of my job applications or a summary of my current financial status upon request. My goal is to establish a sustainable payment plan that reflects my current reality while ensuring the loan is eventually repaid in full.\\n\\nPlease let me know which documents are required to formalize this hardship application. I am also available for a phone call at*+1-765-532-5183* to discuss this further.\\n\\nThank you for your understanding and for helping me find a path forward during this difficult transition.\\n\\nPS: I sent a formal hardship and restructuring request for Loans PDGUS493193 and PDGUS551765 on January 15th. Can you please confirm it has been received and assigned to a case manager?\\n\\nBest regards\\n\\nDarshita Patel", "date_and_timestamp": "1/27/2026 16:30", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_3"}, {"message_content": "Dear Prodigy Finance Collections/Payments Team,\\n\\nI am writing to formally address the overdue status of my account (Loan ID: PDGUS493193 & PDGUS551765). I am currently 90 days past due on my installments, and I am reaching out to resolve this situation before the account moves toward default proactively.\\n\\nI am currently experiencing severe financial hardship due to involuntary unemployment following the completion of my studies. Despite an intensive job search, I have not yet secured a stable income. As an international graduate, I am committed to fulfilling my debt obligations, but my current lack of liquidity makes it impossible to meet the standard monthly installments at this moment.\\n\\nI value my relationship with Prodigy Finance and wish to keep my account in good standing. I would like to request the following formally:\\n\\n1.\\nA temporary suspension of payments for the next few months to allow me to finalize my employment search.\\n2.\\nI request a restructuring of my loan terms. This could include extending the total loan tenure to reduce monthly installments or moving to \\"interest-only\\" payments for a set period.\\n\\nI am eager to cooperate with your team. I can provide documentation of my job applications or a summary of my current financial status upon request. My goal is to establish a sustainable payment plan that reflects my current reality while ensuring the loan is eventually repaid in full.\\n\\nPlease let me know which documents are required to formalize this hardship application. I am also available for a phone call at*+1-765-532-5183* to discuss this further.\\n\\nThank you for your understanding and for helping me find a path forward during this difficult transition.\\n\\nPS: I sent a formal hardship and restructuring request for Loans PDGUS493193 and PDGUS551765 on January 15th. Can you please confirm it has been received and assigned to a case manager?\\n\\nBest regards\\n\\nDarshita Patel", "date_and_timestamp": "1/26/2026 16:30", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_3"}, {"message_content": "Hi Darshitaben\\n \\nI hope you're doing well.\\n \\nMy name is Cheryl, and I’m your Account Manager here at Prodigy Finance. I recently tried calling you on +1 7655325183 - are you still using this number?  If not, please update your contact details in the Prodigy Finance app or share your preferred number with me.\\n \\nWe’ve noticed that your loan payment of USD 1,244.80 for November 2025 hasn’t been received yet. We want to work with you to get things back on track as soon as possible.\\n \\nWhen payments fall behind, there can be serious consequences:\\nYour loan may be reported as in arrears to the Credit Bureau, which can affect your credit score and your ability to access credit in the future.\\nInterest continues to build on missed payments, increasing the overall cost of your loan.\\nIf arrears remain unpaid, your loan could be classified as in default and referred for legal recovery.\\n \\nTo avoid this, we kindly ask that you make a payment of USD 2,474.53 by 28 December 2025. This includes both your missed instalment and the current month's due amount.\\n \\nIf you’re paying from a US, UK, or EU account, setting up auto-debit via the Prodigy Finance app is the simplest way to avoid missing future payments. You can check our FAQs to get started.\\n \\nIf you have any questions or need help making your payment, please don’t hesitate to reach out. You can also schedule a call with the team. We’d be happy to assist.\\n \\nLooking forward to hearing from you.\\n \\nSpeak soon\\nCheryl", "date_and_timestamp": "12/17/2025 11:30", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_3"}], "_payment_count": 2, "_conversation_count": 5, "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_3"}	\N		10	Customer email from 2026-01-27: 'I am currently experiencing severe financial hardship due to involuntary unemployment following the completion of my studies... my current lack of liquidity makes it impossible to meet the standard monthly installments'.	Offer a Forbearance / Payment Holiday. This provides temporary relief while she secures employment, directly aligning with her request and the policy for customers with very low affordability but high willingness.	10	Matches Decision Rule 7 (Affordability=VERY LOW, Willingness=HIGH -> Forbearance). Also directly responds to the customer's request on 2026-01-27 for 'A temporary suspension of payments for the next few months'.		0	Based on zero successful payments in the last 3 months and the customer's direct statement of 'involuntary unemployment' and it being 'impossible to meet the standard monthly installments at this moment'.	0	Subject: Regarding your Hardship Application\n\nBody: Dear Darshita,\n\nThank you for your patience while we review your request. We understand this is a difficult time for you while you search for employment, and we want to find a solution together.\n\nTo move forward with your application for a temporary payment suspension, our specialist team requires the three months of recent bank statements we requested in our last email. This is a crucial step for us to assess and approve the right support for you.\n\nPlease reply to this email with the documents at your earliest convenience. We are here to help you get back on track.\n\nBest regards,\n\nThe Prodigy Finance Team	{"willingness": "HIGH", "combined_cmd": null, "conversation": "Customer proactively emailed in late January 2026 stating severe financial hardship due to post-study unemployment. She explicitly requested a temporary payment suspension and loan restructure. In Feb/Mar, an agent requested bank statements to process her application.", "affordability": "VERY LOW", "customer_guid": "customer_id_3", "vulnerability": false, "ability_to_pay": 0, "internal_action": "", "payment_history": "Last 6 months: 2 cancelled ($2.00). No successful payments in this period.", "problem_evidence": "Customer email from 2026-01-27: 'I am currently experiencing severe financial hardship due to involuntary unemployment following the completion of my studies... my current lack of liquidity makes it impossible to meet the standard monthly installments'.", "proposed_solution": "Offer a Forbearance / Payment Holiday. This provides temporary relief while she secures employment, directly aligning with her request and the policy for customers with very low affordability but high willingness.", "solution_evidence": "Matches Decision Rule 7 (Affordability=VERY LOW, Willingness=HIGH -> Forbearance). Also directly responds to the customer's request on 2026-01-27 for 'A temporary suspension of payments for the next few months'.", "problem_description": "", "arrears_clearance_plan": null, "reason_for_willingness": "Customer proactively emailed in late January 2026 stating severe financial hardship due to post-study unemployment. She explicitly requested a temporary payment suspension and loan restructure. In Feb/Mar, an agent requested bank statements to process her application. → HIGH", "problem_confidence_score": 10, "reason_for_affordability": "Based on zero successful payments in the last 3 months and the customer's direct statement of 'involuntary unemployment' and it being 'impossible to meet the standard monthly installments at this moment'. → VERY LOW", "reason_for_vulnerability": "", "reason_for_ability_to_pay": "Based on zero successful payments in the last 3 months and the customer's direct statement of 'involuntary unemployment' and it being 'impossible to meet the standard monthly installments at this moment'.", "solution_confidence_score": 10, "proposed_email_to_customer": "Subject: Regarding your Hardship Application\\n\\nBody: Dear Darshita,\\n\\nThank you for your patience while we review your request. We understand this is a difficult time for you while you search for employment, and we want to find a solution together.\\n\\nTo move forward with your application for a temporary payment suspension, our specialist team requires the three months of recent bank statements we requested in our last email. This is a crucial step for us to assess and approve the right support for you.\\n\\nPlease reply to this email with the documents at your earliest convenience. We are here to help you get back on track.\\n\\nBest regards,\\n\\nThe Prodigy Finance Team", "no_of_latest_payments_failed": 0}	pending	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	2026-04-07 09:38:02.627861	88bb298f-0fd9-407b-ad75-1ed7ae2ac794
