2	1	Reaging / Re-amortization	Resetting the delinquency clock back to current after the customer demonstrates good behavior (e.g., 3 consecutive on-time payments). The past-due status is wiped. Sometimes combined with capitalizing the arrears into the remaining loan balance.	t	2	Supportive	0	\N	\N	\N	\N
