 my employment search.\\n2.\\nI request a restructuring of my loan terms. This could include extending the total loan tenure to reduce monthly installments or moving to \\"interest-only\\" payments for a set period.\\n\\nI am eager to cooperate with your team. I can provide documentation of my job applications or a summary of my current financial status upon request. My goal is to establish a sustainable payment plan that reflects my current reality while ensuring the loan is eventually repaid in full.\\n\\nPlease let me know which documents are required to formalize this hardship application. I am also available for a phone call at*+1-765-532-5183* to discuss this further.\\n\\nThank you for your understanding and for helping me find a path forward during this difficult transition.\\n\\nPS: I sent a formal hardship and restructuring request for Loans PDGUS493193 and PDGUS551765 on January 15th. Can you please confirm it has been received and assigned to a case manager?\\n\\nBest regards\\n\\nDarshita Patel", "date_and_timestamp": "1/27/2026 16:30", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_3"}, {"_status": "created", "_message": "Created successfully", "message_content": "Dear Prodigy Finance Collections/Payments Team,\\n\\nI am writing to formally address the overdue status of my account (Loan ID: PDGUS493193 & PDGUS551765). I am currently 90 days past due on my installments, and I am reaching out to resolve this situation before the account moves toward default proactively.\\n\\nI am currently experiencing severe financial hardship due to involuntary unemployment following the completion of my studies. Despite an intensive job search, I have not yet secured a stable income. As an international graduate, I am committed to fulfilling my debt obligations, but my current lack of liquidity makes it impossible to meet the standard monthly installments at this moment.\\n\\nI value my relationship with Prodigy Finance and wish to keep my account in good standing. I would like to request the following formally:\\n\\n1.\\nA temporary suspension of payments for the next few months to allow me to finalize my employment search.\\n2.\\nI request a restructuring of my loan terms. This could include extending the total loan tenure to reduce monthly installments or moving to \\"interest-only\\" payments for a set period.\\n\\nI am eager to cooperate with your team. I can provide documentation of my job applications or a summary of my current financial status upon request. My goal is to establish a sustainable payment plan that reflects my current reality while ensuring the loan is eventually repaid in full.\\n\\nPlease let me know which documents are required to formalize this hardship application. I am also available for a phone call at*+1-765-532-5183* to discuss this further.\\n\\nThank you for your understanding and for helping me find a path forward during this difficult transition.\\n\\nPS: I sent a formal hardship and restructuring request for Loans PDGUS493193 and PDGUS551765 on January 15th. Can you please confirm it has been received and assigned to a case manager?\\n\\nBest regards\\n\\nDarshita Patel", "date_and_timestamp": "1/26/2026 16:30", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_3"}, {"_status": "created", "_message": "Created successfully", "message_content": "Hi Darshitaben\\n \\nI hope you're doing well.\\n \\nMy name is Cheryl, and I’m your Account Manager here at Prodigy Finance. I recently tried calling you on +1 7655325183 - are you still using this number?  If not, please update your contact details in the Prodigy Finance app or share your preferred number with me.\\n \\nWe’ve noticed that your loan payment of USD 1,244.80 for November 2025 hasn’t been received yet. We want to work with you to get things back on track as soon as possible.\\n \\nWhen payments fall behind, there can be serious consequences:\\nYour loan may be reported as in arrears to the Credit Bureau, which can affect your credit score and your ability to access credit in the future.\\nInterest continues to build on missed payments, increasing the overall cost of your loan.\\nIf arrears remain unpaid, your loan could be classified as in default and referred for legal recovery.\\n \\nTo avoid this, we kindly ask that you make a payment of USD 2,474.53 by 28 December 2025. This includes both your missed instalment and the current month's due amount.\\n \\nIf you’re paying from a US, UK, or EU account, setting up auto-debit via the Prodigy Finance app is the simplest way to avoid missing future payments. You can check our FAQs to get started.\\n \\nIf you have any questions or need help making your payment, please don’t hesitate to reach out. You can also schedule a call with the team. We’d be happy to assist.\\n \\nLooking forward to hearing from you.\\n \\nSpeak soon\\nCheryl", "date_and_timestamp": "12/17/2025 11:30", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_3"}, {"_status": "created", "_message": "Created successfully", "message_content": "Hi Dheeraj\\n \\nI hope you are doing well.\\n \\nMy name is Andisiwe, and I’m your Account Manager here at Prodigy Finance.\\n \\nWe noticed your Prodigy account is now two months in arrears, and we want to help you get back on track. When payments fall behind, there can be serious consequences:\\nYour loan may be reported as in arrears to the Credit Bureau, which can affect your credit score and your ability to access credit in the future.\\nInterest continues to build on missed payments, increasing the overall cost of your loan.\\nIf arrears remain unpaid, your loan could be classified as in default and referred for legal recovery.\\n \\nWe know life doesn’t always go as planned, and catching up on arrears can feel tough. That’swhy we’ve made it simpler to get your loan back on track.\\n\\nHow it works\\n1. Make consistent payments:\\nPay at least three consecutive contractual monthly installments by the payment due\\ndate, either manually or through auto-debit.\\n\\n2. Choose auto-debit (recommended):\\nSet it up in minutes by logging in, adding your bank details, and choosing your preferred\\ndate.\\n\\n3. We’ll reset your schedule:\\nOnce you’ve made three on-time payments, we’ll roll your arrears into your loan balance\\nand spread it across your remaining term so you can move forward with a clean slate.\\n\\n(Your monthly installment may rise slightly, but your loan will stay on track.)\\n\\nWhy auto-debit helps\\n● Hassle-free: Payments happen automatically , no reminders or manual transfers.\\n● On time, every time: Auto-debit means payments land on time, every time.\\n● Stay current: A steady payment history helps keep your loan and credit in good\\nstanding.\\n\\nIf you’re eligible, we recommend setting up auto-debit today—it takes less than two minutes.\\n[Set up auto-debit]\\n\\nIf auto-debit isn’t available for you right now, don’t worry. You can still make your three consecutive contractual payments to your Prodigy Finance account to qualify.\\n\\nIf you have any questions, reply to this email or reach out via your account, we’re here to help.\\n\\nSpeak soon,\\nAndisiwe", "date_and_timestamp": "2/13/2026 13:25", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"_status": "created", "_message": "Created successfully", "message_content": "Hi Dheeraj,\\n \\nThank you for calling in yesterday — it was a pleasure speaking with you.\\n \\nAs discussed during our call, you’re currently unable to repay the full outstanding balance on your loans (including arrears) due to being unemployed. You contacted us to explore the available options and advised that, at this stage, you can afford to make a payment of approximately USD 800.00 toward your loans.\\n \\nBelow is a breakdown of the current outstanding balance for each loan:\\n \\nPDGUS506522\\nPayment due on 28 January 2026: USD 716.01\\nContractual monthly amount: USD 238.90\\nAccumulated arrears: USD 477.11\\nInterest rate: 9.03%\\n \\nPDGUS305344\\nPayment due on 28 January 2026: USD 381.32\\nContractual monthly amount: USD 190.66\\nAccumulated arrears: USD 190.66\\nInterest rate: 9.68%\\n \\nPDGUS326885\\nPayment due on 28 January 2026: USD 835.88\\nContractual monthly amount: USD 417.93\\nAccumulated arrears: USD 417.95\\nInterest rate: 9.52%\\n \\nTo bring your account fully back on schedule this month, a total payment of USD 1,933.21 would be required. However, as you mentioned this is not currently affordable, we recommend making a minimum payment of USD 847.49 by 28 January 2026. This will help prevent your loans from falling further into arrears or moving into a more serious collections stage.\\n \\nAdditionally, our records show that you have already used 6 months of forbearance - to date. However, if your financial circumstances do not improve and you would like to explore further forbearance, please feel free to reach out. We can then share the relevant information and assessment for you to complete. Please note that, if approved, an additional 3 months of forbearance would be the final forbearance available for the remaining term of your loan.\\n \\nIf you have any questions or would like to discuss the next steps, please don’t hesitate to contact us.\\n \\nKind regards,\\nLynn", "date_and_timestamp": "1/13/2026 11:13", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"_status": "created", "_message": "Created successfully", "message_content": "Hi Dheeraj\\n \\nI hope you're doing well.\\n \\nMy name is Michael, and I’m your Account Manager here at Prodigy Finance. I recently tried calling you on +1 (214) 471-8605 - are you still using this number?  If not, please update your contact details in the Prodigy Finance app or share your preferred number with me.\\n \\nWe want to work with you to get things back on track as soon as possible.\\n \\nWhen payments fall behind, there can be serious consequences:\\nYour loan may be reported as in arrears to the Credit Bureau, which can affect your credit score and your 