ny one of our available arrangement packages. The information provided will remain confidential and is only intended to help us understand your current situation.\\n\\nPlease complete this assessment in its entirety and provide all the requested supporting documentation to be considered for forbearance. This assessment link is custom to your account specifically and should not be shared with others.\\n\\nWe will provide you with feedback within 10 business days from the date that your completed assessment is received.\\n\\nYou must complete all parts of the assessment and submit it to us with all the required supporting documentation for your application to be considered.\\n\\nImportant:\\n\\nIf you select “I recently lost my job” in the assessment, please reply to this email with a copy of your termination letter or separation agreement from your employer.\\n\\nIf you select “I am doing an unpaid internship,” “unpaid employment,” or “voluntary employment,” please reply to this email with a copy of the letter confirming your unpaid internship or voluntary role from your employer or organization.\\n\\nYour application will not be considered complete until we receive these supporting documents by email.\\n\\nImpact of forbearance on auto-debit payments\\n\\nIf you have an auto-debit set up for your payments, you need to ensure that we receive your completed assessment at least ten (10) days before your auto-debit date. This is to ensure that your auto debit settings are adjusted in time to prevent payments from being processed if the request is approved. If we do not receive your request in time, your payment will be debited from your account as normal on the selected date.\\n\\nDue date for submission of forbearance request\\n\\nPlease note that you have 10 days from today to complete and submit your forbearance assessment. If we receive your arrangement request after the 28th of this month and it is approved, your arrangement will only begin from NEXT CYCLE MONTH. This means your regular payment for THIS CYCLE MONTH will still be due as scheduled.\\n\\nIf there’s anything you’d like us to explain further, don’t hesitate to let us know. We’re here to help.\\n\\nSpeak soon,\\nVirtual AI Assistant, Lily", "date_and_timestamp": "2/20/2026 10:38", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_1"}, {"_status": "updated", "_message": "Updated successfully", "message_content": "Hi Sathwik,\\n\\nThank you for letting us know about your financial situation. We understand this may be a stressful time, and we want you to feel supported and fully informed about the options available to you.\\n\\nProdigy is committed to supporting customers in financial hardship, and we want to ensure that you are well informed about the options available and any impact on you. If you are considering requesting forbearance,  please read the information below carefully before submitting your request.\\n\\nWhat is forbearance?\\n\\nIf you want to find out more about Forbearance.\\n\\nIt is important to note that we generally only approve arrangements of up to 6 months within any 12-month timeframe, granted in two 3 month periods and subject to the overall maximum forbearance of 9 months over the entire duration of the loan(s). Each forbearance request is assessed by our specialist team who may request supporting documents to verify the information provided to support the request. Although forbearance can provide temporary relief by allowing you to reduce or pause your payments for a specified period, it is crucial to understand that forbearance should be considered as a last resort. It is always beneficial to explore other options first, before resorting to forbearance.\\n\\nWhat happens during forbearance?\\n\\nIf your loan(s) is placed in an arrangement, the loan agreement terms won’t change. This means that:\\n\\nInterest will still accrue on the outstanding balance while your loan is in an arrangement. This can increase the overall cost of credit, and you 